{
  "texts": [
    "SF, with extremely fine spherical particles between 0.1 and 0.3 µm, has a large surface area that significantly boosts both strength and durability.",
    "POFA typically contains angular, irregular, and porous particles between 20 and 150 µm, which can affect both workability and long-term durability.",
    "ESP consists of irregular particles ranging from 1 to 50 µm, which may impact its ability to bind effectively in concrete.",
    "Bentonite features plate-like particles between 1 and 100 µm, known for their ability to retain water and swell.",
    "Zeolite has a unique crystalline structure with a variety of shapes, including cylindrical, spherical, irregular, and tabular, with particle sizes from 0.5 to 50 µm, allowing for diverse applications based on its unique properties."
  ]
}